A decade ago survey data fromshowed that safety was a number one concern for many passengers using Malaysian public transport KTM Komuter introduced pink coaches then but government didnt really improve safety policies overall

Its time to fix that mistake

Its quite possible that someone took our observation about a possible express rail link to Skypark and ran with it but without the frequencyconnectivity needed to make it work really well

This is why we need integrated public transport solutions

Coordination of routes has been an ongoing issue For example PUTRAB became Putraline B became RapidKL T Unowbut still the same route It could have been rerouted years ago to better serve Sunway as studenttourism demand has grown

Another example The Kelana Jaya LRT feeder bus that served Ara Damansara and Subang Airport could have been rerouted to pass by Subang Jaya Komuter stationSubang Parade long ago

Its little things like this that could improve access and public transport connectivity
We cannot help but wonder ifare asking about this service and whether the rolling stock assets should be deployed differently or elsewhere if the service isnt growing in spite of the free service
After this much time with ongoing free service and poor ridership we have no choice but to ask about the studies behind this service and the opportunity costs associated with continuing the service

The ones who refuse to give Klang Valley Penang etc proper Regional Public Transport Organizing Authority

The ones who treat busrail as separate things and do not push for integration of Prasarana MRT LRT Monorail busKTM Komuter services into one big network
